        "C": "The work does not increase because the height and mass are unchanged. If work increased while time decreased, power would rise even more, but that is not the described comparison.",
        "D": "Correct. Both trials raise the same mass through the same vertical height, so gravitational work is the same. Trial 2 completes that work in half the time, doubling average power."
